column6: Howell and Marlboro locations. Tests are currently limited to 80 patients per day at individual locations.

Since the testing kits are limited
column2: testing may alternate days at certain other locations
column3: so check the Central Jersey Urgent Care website daily for updates.

column5: Community-Based Testing Sites are for individuals who are experiencing symptoms of respiratory illness. In order to be eligible for testing
column6: individuals must be current New Jersey residents and experiencing symptoms of respiratory illness. Priority will be given to symptomatic individuals experiencing cough
column7: fever (99.6F or above) and shortness of breath. The drive-thru testing center will be open seven days per week
column8: beginning at 8:00 a.m. until supplies last. Complete the self-assessment to learn what to do.

column5: Please note that testing is by appointment only and you must be registered through your doctor or healthcare provider. Union County residents
column6: Union County First Responders and essential personnel
column7: who have been instructed by their doctor or healthcare provider to be tested for COVID-19
column8: must be given a prescription and registered by their doctor or healthcare provider on a secure portal where they will receive an appointment for the drive-through. This is the only way to receive an appointment to be tested. For the safety
column9: health and security of the volunteers at the site
column10: the testing location will not allow patients without vehicles to enter campus
column11: even with a valid prescription and appointment. If you do not have your own transportation
column12: please discuss with your healthcare provider before scheduling an appointment
